Adelina Murio-Celli d'Elpeux (1844, Wrocław - April 10, 1900, New York City) was a Polish opera singer, music teacher and composer.
Murio-Celli was born in Breslau of Franco-Russian parents, and went to Paris with them when she was two years old.
When Murio-Celli was 15 years old, she won a prize for singing at the Paris Conservatoire.
In 1870, Murio-Celli retired from singing and began teaching music in Chicago.
In 1880, they moved to New York.
She died April 10, 1900, at her home, New York, of pneumonia.
